That Article, by the way, is looking pretty mistaken as far as cable compan=
ies go: cord cutting isn=E2=80=99t slowing down, and fiber and 5G are makin=
g a dent in home Internet. The underlying point, though, is about the shift=
ing incentives in terms of distribution, and that is exactly why Primetime =
Channels is more viable that it might have been previously. To that end, ca=
ble companies, and the industries that rely on them =E2=80=94 namely, regio=
nal sports networks (RSNs), and by extension the NBA and MLB =E2=80=94 shou=
ld be relieved that Primetime Channels exist.

