d infrastructure costs as cable companies; they operate nationally over the=
 Internet. That means that not carrying RSNs is a rational decision: sure, =
hardcore sports fans won=E2=80=99t choose an MVPD, but that is counterbalan=
ced by being able to offer a lower price relative to cable; cable, meanwhil=
e, can=E2=80=99t afford to lose subscribers who care about RSNs because of =
their high fixed costs. The end result is that while vMVPDs are slowing the=
 rate of cord cutting, they are only doing so for national networks like ES=
PN; RSNs are losing far more customers, to the point where some are teeteri=
ng on bankruptcy, potentially wrecking the economic model for high inventor=
y leagues like professional basketball and football.

If NFL Sunday Ticket were only available on YouTube TV, though, that would =
be a big incentive for sports fans to switch to YouTube TV. Yes, you lose r=
egional sports networks, but you get all of the NFL, and in this case, you =
don=E2=80=99t need to get a satellite dish to do so. That is still a risk, =
but the fact that NFL Sunday Ticket will be easily acquired as a standalone=
 subscription in Primetime Channels means that sports fans can have it all:=
 both regional sports and all of the NFL. That gives RSNs and the leagues t=
hat depend on them a bit more breathing room to figure out the future (or, =
more likely, to kick this very significant can down the road).

